long.am,ar,bg,bn,ca,cs,da,de,el,en,en_AU,en_G:
Easily Transfer Your YouTube Subscriptions

This Chrome extension helps you quickly move your YouTube subscriptions from one account to another using a backup CSV file.

How to Use

1. Backup Your Data:
Use Google Takeout to export your YouTube subscriptions from your old account.

2. Transfer Subscriptions:
Open YouTube and log in to your new account.
Click the extension icon in the Chrome toolbar.
Select your CSV backup file.

Notes

1. Set YouTubeâ€™s language to English or Chinese.
2. The process might take a while depending on how many channels you're subscribing to.

Troubleshooting
1. Check the console for errors if something goes wrong.
2. Make sure your CSV file is correctly formatted.
